					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Before you do that, check if this is really your problem. I suspect you're setting the scroll for the first time too late in the frame, but you can check in FCEUX debugger (there are many threads explaining how to use it).<br /><br />That being said, having the game logic in the NMI handler is a legitemate way to do thing (famous games like SMB do it), but you have to do PPU updates first and game logic second (I don't know if nerdy nights does it like that, but I've seen tutorials that don't), otherwise the VBlank will end before you have processed the entire game state and the PPU updates will spill into rendering time, screwing things up.</div>

